;; mark_distance_skew.synth — mark-type candidate via distance
;; skew (issue 007, July 2026 round).
;;
;; Prior attempts all fed the polymorphism into an ES formal,
;; which stage 1 (type) splits first. This shape decouples the
;; two ingredients mark-type needs:
;;   1. the SEED type confluence lives only at a CS-contour
;;      field (t.data gets int32 + float64) — stage 1 skips it;
;;   2. the MARKED confluence lives at sink()'s monomorphic
;;      int32 formal, fed by the same int constant along two
;;      paths of different flow length (direct vs through
;;      relay()). different_marked_args is distance-sensitive,
;;      so the long-path edge's key set diverges from the
;;      short-path edge's at the formal.
;;
;; Golden documents what actually fires.

shape: mark_distance_skew
